Author: dogebearman
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: It's pretty obvious that this was an exit scam. I remember a few months back (I think in August) there was a section on the WiC website which was showing the pictures and names of three allegeded team members (2 male, 1 female).  But nobody was able to find any information regarding these names or pictures, the only thing someone found was that the picture of the female allegeded team meber has been shared on a twitter account which only features pictures of blonde women. After the user Infantoo pointed this out here in this thread (https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2043933.msg21393478#msg21393478) he deleted the section about the "team" on the website. But it's still available here https://icobench.com/ico/wic/team  Try your luck and search for information about Ronald B. Sao, Catherine Oliver and Deepak Kumar. You won't find any because WiC is just one person who made a good amount of money by scamming a lot of people.

Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Just a couple of questions.  -You didn't made any transactions you said last month, but did you log in to MEW with your json file (or any other means)? -you mention the thief as https://etherscan.io/address/0x5e4abe6419650ca839ce5bb7db422b881a6064bb but the transaction you showed was: https://ethplorer.io/tx/0xf991bce92f86e3e890fc1ec0bdf35bf746fc1d6aed24182d07884202a63f4ed2 that has as receiving address: https://ethplorer.io/address/0x4f00b95c625c6d6ef72748d78c750fd6c84a8b85 Are you sure about that 0x5e4 address?  that 0x4f address just has 2 WiC transfers: on 2017-11-20: https://ethplorer.io/tx/0x0dd179d358b194c7cc05bcd6a0455ee0869b693c63030ce17214bdeac5352abc#pageSize=25 and yours 2018-01-05: https://ethplorer.io/tx/0xf991bce92f86e3e890fc1ec0bdf35bf746fc1d6aed24182d07884202a63f4ed2#pageSize=25  however, address 0x4f00b95c625c6d6ef72748d78c750fd6c84a8b85 contains a lot of different tokens it looks like it is most likely that you are phished and not caused by a fault in a contract as it would give a lot more WiC transactions to that address.  As 0x5e4abe6419650ca839ce5bb7db422b881a6064bb just brings you to the token/contract address that gives an overview    edit: the date of the transactions were wrong by mistake

Lambo doesnt even care to log on and post on the thread since the tokensale is over.  He made out with our money and ran is what it looks like at this point.  Hopefully he will turn around and the app will get some use and we will see SOME value from WiC coin.... Maybe one day it will go to the value of ICO again, the initial hope was to go over.. but when people start dumping tokens directly after "ICO" for less than they paid it is more than fishy.    Most of ICO tokens could have been bought on livecoin by Lambo/dev from themselves and sold to themselves for cheaper price. Not really losing any of their own money there, since millions were invested in presale before livecoin. That is why presale round 1-3 tokens were locked into deposits for a few days. Couldn't even make a little bit of profit if you tried directly off ICO. That adds to the suspect of the project from the beginning of the ICO finish. Along with the rushed finish for no reason...  Without any active dev reports, support, upgrades, promotion... anything WiC has fallen into the grave.  As I said many other old coins WERE STEADY around 1-2 sat or a little higher for YEARS, then technology picks up and now the coins have exploded. Hopefully that will be the case if people actually adopt WiC and we see movement from the Dev and team.  As of now again it seems like we all were hosed unfortunately. The price in BTC doesnt matter... nobody wants a token that has 0 real world usage.  If there was more development and pushing into furthering the coin and promotion maybe it would stir some interest. But with a dead development team, half working app (only on andriod), this wont be going anywhere anytime soon...  No team, no furthering project, no promotion, and stuck only on LiveCoin with near 0 volume at all, 174$ in past 24hrs   hopefully not all the way to 1 sat.  If its a total loss then its a total loss.. been there done that. Again I'm more then glad I sold over half my tokens straight away for slightly higher than the .008 cents I paid for them.  If theres any furthering on the project, perhaps ill pick up more for the mere fractions of a penny that they are at now.

I know its unfortunate but its definitely not the end and we will never give up. Thanks for all your support Stay tuned for more updates. Author: maxiseven
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: The reply from Lambo: WiC Hey, so first of all I would like to make it clear that we are still here and will be continuously working on WiC. So please don't spread FUD [...] Also, I would want to inform [...] that the 2 days approval timeline is for old accounts who have published before and not new ones. Since this is the first app it will take time and that is how it is. Not much we can do about that from our end. I understand everyone is frustrated with the price, but please understand that this is not something we can control or would want to manipulate. WiC is not a pump and dump coin and we will never want it to be one. As far as progress on the project and updates are concerened I appreciate everyone's enthusiasm here but please understand that these things take time and there is no way we can publish new news every other week. I have also never believed in comparing WiC with other projects, but if you look at coinmarketcap most coins there have either no product at all and are purely speculative or have no updates for months or have volume similar to ours. Again, we are still here, still working on updates and can assure you WiC will not die. Thanks!

Author: niceli
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Right. First of all I think it is great that we are sticking to the planned timing and get the app released so early.  It will be important that the quality of the app is right and I hope that new features will be rolled out on a regularly basis. One cruical feature for me would be that you can buy WiC conviently in the app using paypal or similar fiat tools in future. Not all users should be forced to make accounts in crypto exchanges in order to load up WiC. Probably there could be a 5% fee or something like that if you use this service in order to still drive the crypto adption forward.  Also it will be important that we get the roll out of the iOS version soon. Best would be if Lambo could provide us with a roadmap.  Most cruical thing for the price itself will be to get onto more and bigger(paid) exchanges. It will required to use some of the ICO money for exchange listing. And of course we need a lot of marketing. Here we also need an update from Lambo about which activities are being carried out, what is planned and where the user base might be able to support.  When all of this is handled professionally we might see huge gains with WiC in 2018.

Author: ScoreB
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Could someone explain the benefits of using WiC App in highly populated areas like major cities? I'd say as soon as a few people "sell" their wifi, in order to compete with these and draw any traffic to your own hotspot your price would soon need to drop to near zero.. furthermore, in a highly populated area chances of people misusing your wifi and causing you legal problems seem quite real..  I've read the devs statement on page 1 that misuse is unlikely since people wanting to commit harm would be more likely to go to a free-WiFi spot at like MacDonalds rather then pay WiC for yours.. this logic however (to me) seems broken. For if there is a free-WiFi spot nearby why would anyone else rather choose to pay WiC for yours? Could be bandwidth/connection speed but the same would apply for scammers etc.. Also, everyone knows that at free-WiFi spots there is usually a ton of logging taking place.. while if you could use someones private WiFi you'd be much more anonymous..  So, as far as I see it.. high risks (misuse of your WiFi causing you legal problems) for small / neglectable gains.  In more remote locations where WiFi spots are (very) scarce it might be profitable to run the app but it would still be (in my eyes) a huge security risk and you probably won't draw a lot of traffic in less densely populated zones (so again, not much to gain..).  If anyone could explain me why I'm looking at this the wrong way round, please explain .  ---  PS: If the price goes to moon because of pure speculation however, it might still be fun to buy and hodl a few and sell at peak..

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: No minimum requirement. You can buy for any amount  To participate in the Token Sale:  1) Create an account on Livecoin.net: https://www.livecoin.net/en/site/registration  2) Deposit BTC or ETH in your account.  3) To participate with BTC, visit: https://goo.gl/hx7yE1  4) To participate with ETH, visit: https://goo.gl/gZvErd  5) You might need to place the buy order for your amount minus livecoin fees (0.18%) since some users experience that they get an error if they put the entire amount. This is probably a minor error on livecoin.net.  6) Tokens will be withdrawable 1-2 days after the token sale is completed.

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey,  So yes we have a press release scheduled to release this week and an article pushed by ICOlert to 14,000+ users today or tomorrow. This will be done even we reduce the Token Sale duration.  We will not be using the unsold tokens for WiC reloadable cards as explained earlier. Will paste that below for convenience sake:  "We will not be buying back WiC or funding the reloadable cards with the 5% which is reserved solely for in-app distribution. The customer who wants to buy a reloadable card will pay in fiat and the seller of the cards will buy the exact amount of WiC at that moment's price and forward it to the customer. So that means the seller will not have pre-bought WiC but will buy as per the customer demands."  Also, we do not intend to sell the unsold 50% tokens on the market since selling it so early will be not be ideal and we expect the prices to rise much more than what they are now. We will sell only in small quantities and only as and when needed.  Thanks!

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: @Pab @amacar1 @xpzycox  Even we initially wanted to run it for the full length but keep in mind the China ICO news too. Although it is completely irrelevant to us, we are not sure how it might affect Livecoin and how they will react to it.  Most of the contributions usually come during the start and end of the token sale so the in-between period is usually the "slow period". And if we cut short the Token Sale on Livecoin, we also mitigate the China/Livecoin risk (this is nothing major as of now) while not losing a lot since this will as it is be a slow contribution period.  Let us know what you think about it  Thanks!

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, let me try to explain how it will work:  We will not be buying back WiC or funding the reloadable cards with the 5% which is reserved solely for in-app distribution.  The customer who wants to buy a reloadable card will pay in fiat and the seller of the cards will buy the exact amount of WiC at that moment's price and forward it to the customer. So that means the seller will not have pre-bought WiC but will buy as per the customer demands.  Hope that clarifies it. If there is any further questions, feel free to ask me.  Thanks!

Author: crsbee
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Cool, thank you for the clarification! I think the idea is good because it bases the wic/fiat exchange purely on the market.  The only doubt I would have is regarding the simplicity. As far as I understand, other giftcards already contain a code or similar which often needs to be scratched off and then have a fixed amount of something (e.g. "itunes money") on it. If I understand your approach correctly now, users can buy wallets on plastic cards and retailers need some sort of terminal in order to load them up with wic. In order to make this work in a bulletproof way I am guessing that you would need provide hardware with pre-installed software to the retailer which would connect to a service you are hosting which allows for quick and easy loading up of the cards using best market conditions. Would that assumption be correct or do you have other plans (like e.g. only having wic cards available at specially trained retailers)?

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Having a special hardware terminal will be quite expensive especially if we have to deliver it to thousands of stores across the world. An easier way would be to train them or give manuals on how to buy WiC and load it on to the cards.  You must have heard of paper wallets right? Gift cards can essentially have the same concept as in the public key will be open and used by the retailers to load up the desired amount of WiC and the private key will have to be scratched off by the consumer.  This is not set in stone though and we might have improvements and changes when we are closer on implementing this.  Thanks!

The whole idea behind WiC is convenience of easily being to find a wifi hotspot around your area. If they have to now find a retailer that sells gift cards, it ruins the experience. I think a easy online method of buying credit is absolutely crucial for the success of WiC

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: We have a plan to issue WiC re-loadable cards. This will be something like gift cards and be available at retail convenience stores and gas stations. We are currently focusing on the Token Sale and smooth launch of the app. After that the main focus will be on mass adoption. Once we have a loyal user base, we will go on to approach companies for distributing the WiC reloadable cards.  Something from the whitepaper:  "Another thing we intend to do is have WiC reloadable cards available at gas stations and retail convenience stores, so that people even without the knowledge of crypto currencies will be able to use our app without issues. How this will work is similar to how reloadable gift cards work. Users will have the option to use their local currency at local outlets that will give them pre-loaded unscratched WiC cards with private keys that can be used to load the purchased balance in to the CryptoWi app. This way we eliminate the need for the end user to know how crypto currencies work and make WiFi sharing easy and hassle free."  Thanks!

Author: Stroto
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: The majority of people do not care about safety when using a free wifi anywhere, so why would they when using WiC? In any case for someone that wants to have data, it would be easier to hide an a free public network then when doing so on a router that has a location connected to them.  Guest networks are not that hard and at least where I live rather the norm when visiting someone. VpN is depending on your router, but in most cases as easy as uploading a file and turn it on.

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, creating guest networks running on VPN is one option for those that would want to do this. It is not compulsory though.  Also, as far as issues regarding illegal activity are concerned, there is no real incentive to use our app for illegal purposes since it would create unnecessary issues for that person. He could easily go to a Starbucks or McDonalds and use their WiFi; no reason to download this app, then buy WiC and then pay for it. We will also have a point in our terms and conditions that anybody using someone's WiFi is solely responsible for his actions and the owner is not liable for this user's actions. The owner will also have proof that someone else used the WiFi at a particular date and time since the app will have a record of this.

Author: EleanorZ
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: You're not wrong, but the fact is LinkedIn profiles can also be made up, or scammers can list the profiles of people who in real life have never heard of the ICO in question. Every ICO, short of, like, the brainchild of Vitalik Buterin and Da Hongfei, carries quite a bit of risk, and anyone who spends money on them that they can't afford is asking for trouble. You take a risk, and maybe you get rewarded or maybe you lose it all.  But more importantly, what are the incentives for a scammer? If the goal is to take the money and run, there are easier ways of doing it than the path WiC has been on (30+ pages on the original thread this spring, and now almost 90 on this one, active engagement with the community, partnerships with livecoin and reputable escrow-ers, etc.). You're unlikely to go through all that if you don't even plan to send out tokens. And if you do send out tokens, you might as well follow through with the idea at least far enough to pump the thing and get even more $$ out of it. In the latter case, ICO participants likely also do well.  The point is probably 1 ICO in 100 actually succeeds in the bigger picture, but from the perspective of the investor, ICOs are more about short-term profit than they are about finding the next ETH. With that in mind, the standards for judging the merits of an ICO change somewhat. It's less about 'will this really succeed?' and more about 'will this appeal to the extremely Lambo-obsessed crypto community enough to capture their attention and spike in value after release?".

Author: paraelement
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: I apologize for going offtopic in advance, but I feel our conversation may be of some use for other forum members.  I agree that any ICO is a risk, then it's up to you how do you choose to mitigate the risk and maximize success when making the decision whether to participate - this is what I'm mostly ranting about.  The incentives for a would-be-scammer are money from ICO, and I think there are plenty. Note that I'm not saying CryptoWi is a scam and I'll be happy if in a couple of years I can walk streets of, say, Madrid, as a tourist, while enjoying Wi-Fi access through CryptoWi app. But still.  Possibly, we assess the effort and costs differently, but lets look what we have: 1) thread for 130 pages on the forum where someone would post news, answer questions etc 2) create, host, maintain a website (without any complex functionality and amateurish-looking, to be honest) 3) develop "application prototype" shown on videos 4) maintain telegram channel/facebook page 5) promote on steemit, medium, icolert, some other crypto media sites? 6) escrow anything else I missed? My estimate for pp.1-4 is more than $50k. I dont know how much p.5 and 6 cost, but I doubt the total would exceed $200k. Even if I'm wrong and underestimating the costs for 2-3 times, there is still plenty of incentive, and I'm not aware of an easier way of doing a million dollars in a few months (pls PM me if you do )  As for the ICO model you've described - I understood it as a pyramid. Get tokens earlier, sell them later to someone else for inflated price, move on. So yeah, as in any pyramid, some people will make money.  But how do you think, would this make more people put more trust into ICOs/crypto as a whole? Wouldn't it actually harm the crypto industry (still in its puberty, if not childhood) if there are two projects on the similar topic, but one of them is a pyramid? Would scams cause more attention and regulation attempts from the government? I agree that very little percentage of ICOs are successful projects - basically, as any startups - but by participating in pyramid-like ICOs we ourselves are making this percentage even smaller, aren't we?  So, however naive and pompously this may sound, I'm all for investing only in the projects that wouldn't consider a pyramid, to ultimately help mass adoption of crypto and personal gain, rather than personal gain alone. Thanks for reading this, apologies for offtopic once again, and sorry for any mistakes in my English.

Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey Lambo06 and Crypto Wi team,  got a couple of questions, possibly they were asked before but it's hard to browse 100+ in both threads and there is no FAQ anywhere AFAIK, so:  1) Who are the guys on the team? There is too little information on them here or in search engines, can you post their Facebook/Linkedin profiles here and on the website?  2) What does exactly one buys with Wic? I mean, buying password itself is useless.  3) If you buy access to someone's wifi, is it limited by duration, total usage time, total traffic? If it is, can the owner set any or all of these parameters?  4) If I buy a password, use wifi for some time, and then the connection is lost (owner chooses to change password, turns wifi off, a dozen of other reasons), what happens?  5) If I buy a password and find the connection quality inadequate (for legitimate reasons, or because the owner uses traffic shaping, noone knows), what happens (any refund mechanics)?  6) Is there a desktop (PC/Mac/*nix) version of the application planned?   Thanks in advance for the answers, they should greatly improve confidence in the project!

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey,  1) The team is actually bigger than what is posted and only the lead from each department is posted. We are getting legal advise and also hiring some legal experts because of the complex environment regarding Token Sales and will publish details once we get the go ahead from legal. You might, for example, know that making an app (that too this complex) is not a one man job and Deepak is just the development team lead. There are around a total of 12-15 members in the team including full time employees, independent contractors and interns. Also, we have actually gone ahead, spent money and time and developed a real product the demo video of which has been posted. Also, both the Presale and the Token Sale will also be fully escrowed by highly reputed members of the community for your safety.  2) WiC is the only mode of payment accepted in the app and hence it is used to buy WiFi. Don't see how that is uselss though. In fact this gives WiC a real world use case.  3) At the moment, the WiFi user pays a one time fee for the network but we plan to introduce a feature where the uploader will specify aminimum and maximum time and data limit for the connection and the buyer will be able to see this before purchasing.  4) For the above mentioned reason, the amount paid will be lost as of now. But we will be changing this with future updates.  5)There are no refund mechanics as of now and we plan to introduce features where users will be able to rate WiFi networks and also upload speed test results.  6) No, only mobile apps for now.  Thanks!

Body: Sorry guys I have another question, sort of new to the crypto world. So once I pay and receive the tokens, I'm assuming it's going to be in Eth. How will I then exchange it to WiC to trade with? I'm sure this has been answered so maybe point me to a resource would be fine. Thanks.

Author: EleanorZ
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Not quite. Ethereum is a blockchain platform on which other applications can run. WiC tokens are Ethereum ERC20 tokens--that is, WiC is an independently developed project whose tokens run on Ethereum's blockchain. There is no WiC independent of the Ethereum blockchain (this is not unique; e.g., EOS, GNT, PAY, OMG, 0x, and many other big names are Ethereum tokens).  So, you paid X amount of money to the WiC devs in BTC, LTC, or ETH (in this case, ETH is being used simply as a 'coin'), which entitles you to Y number of WiC tokens. When you bought your tokens, you had to specify an Ethereum ERC20-compatible address--that is, you need an Ethereum wallet that supports tokens that run on the ERC20 standard. Later, when WiC tokens are distributed, they will be sent to this address. Since they are Ethereum ERC20 tokens and not something with an independent blockchain, you will always use an Ethereum wallet to manage them. You would trade these tokens--no additional exchanging. The tokens you receive into your Ethereum wallet are as real as your WiC will ever get.  More resources on Ethereum tokens here:  https://blog.coinbase.com/a-beginners-guide-to-ethereum-tokens-fbd5611fe30b  https://blockgeeks.com/guides/ethereum-token/

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Quote from: xpzycox on August 27, 2017, 04:07:46 PM anasso has a point I think... I know I'm a newbie here but not too new to crypto world.  I've invested a great deal in stage 1 and I believe in this project highly, but as to the WiFi sharing.  As anasso stated, basically if a user has no wic or doesnt know about crypto they wouldnt be able to get the shared wifi.  How would they be able to add WiC to their account or whatever, is their only way is to buy it on livecoin?  Hey, we have thought about this and understand that the majority of the people either do not know about crypto or do not want to get involved with it for various reasons. To solve this issue we will be taking several steps to make WiC purchases easy for the average user. Some of the major ones are as below (sourced from the whitepaper):  WiC/Local currency exchange – Another planned feature, aimed at making the end user experience smooth and hassle free is enabling the ability to buy WiC directly from the app using traditional payment methods like debit/credit cards and net banking. The main purpose of this is to make it easy for those users who do not want to get involved with crypto currencies in any way and just want access to cheap and reliable WiFi.  Another thing we intend to do is have WiC reloadable cards available at gas stations and retail convenience stores, so that people even without the knowledge of crypto currencies will be able to use our app without issues. How this will work is similar to how reloadable gift cards work. Users will have the option to use their local currency at local outlets that will give them pre-loaded unscratched WiC cards with private keys that can be used to load the purchased balance in to the CryptoWi app. This way we eliminate the need for the end user to know how crypto currencies work and make WiFi sharing easy and hassle free.

Author: EleanorZ
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: They made their public announcement on August 1, so WiC may have caused them to speed up their release but I doubt they came up with their idea solely as a response to WiC.  The two ideas seem quite different in scope regardless. Ammbr is trying to build its own network from scratch, with users acquiring and deploying dedicated Ambrr routers. It would be huge if successful, but there are a lot of barriers to success, not least of which is the development and roll-out of the router device itself. It's unclear if they even have a working prototype at this time. In that respect, it's more like a self-driving car or SpaceX's Hyperloop--a neat idea that's still a long way from actual mainstream adoption.  WiC is leveraging existing technologies to essentially crowdsource internet access. It may not have the wow factor, but it's very doable in real life. It's more like Uber or Airbnb--simple ideas that disrupted their respective industries. Who knows if WiC can pull that off for internet access, but in the short term I don't see WiC and Ammbr as direct competitors. WiC's marketing strategy should probably emphasize that fact, too.

Author: EleanorZ
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: 2 million WiC are allocated for bounties, of which 20%, or 400,000, are for signatures. Bounties are almost always speculative. Like, if you do a translation, maybe you get 500 or 1000 WiC (I'm making those numbers up based on experience with other coins; no idea what WiC is planning), which is nothing if you go by $0.008/WiC, but that's not a real, market-based price. We have no idea what WiC will be worth when it hits markets, but it's going to be more than $0.008 unless something goes horribly wrong. As a bounty hunter (and, frankly, as investors in the ICO) you're gambling that WiC will be worth 25 cents, 50 cents, a buck, even a few bucks, at which point getting those 500 or 1000 WiC 'for free' is a pretty tidy return for a couple of hours' work. That's why every new ANN thread has a million 'Indonesian translation reserved'-type posts in the first couple of pages.

Author: EleanorZ
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Invested a little on day 1, so I hope this succeeds. However, some questions:  1. Are there any plans to allocate funds for professional branding in the future (like a few months to a year from now)? I think a stronger brand (logo + name) would help with mainstream adoption.  2. If you go to a new country and want to use the CryptoWi app to find a connection, I'm assuming you already need internet access in order to view the map and search for available connections. Is there any way to get around this 'paradox'?  3. Will there be any kind of legal protection for the people sharing their connections, e.g. in case someone uses their connection to do something illegal?  Thanks for all your time and effort on this so far.

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, thanks for supporting us on day 1! As for your questions:  1) We have allocated 50% of the funds raised for marketing purposes so depending on the total amount raised we will be doing this. 2) Yes, there is a planned feature update where you will be able to pre-download WiFi spots of any area and also navigate in offline mode. 3) As far as issues regarding illegal activity are concerned, there is no real incentive to use our app for illegal purposes since it would create unnecessary issues for that person. He could easily go to a Starbucks or McDonalds and use their WiFi; no reason to download this app, then buy WiC and then pay for it. Also, there will be a record when someone uses your WiFi since he will pay you for it. So if someone uses it for any wrong purpose you will have proof of sharing it. And we will also have it in our terms and conditions that anyone buying a shared network is responsible for what he does online and not the owner of the network.

Author: bandar
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: I invested some & it does look promising.  But as an advocate of non-crypto-people I have some simple non-crypto questions:  Let's say people like to use this app.  In the whitepaper I read they use Wicoins for this.  Though as an investment incentive for cryptopeople this looks like gold when millions use this app, the price will fluctuate.  Let's say you buy 100 WIC for $100, you'd have some expextations about how long you'd be able to connect.  You don't want to buy 100 WIC and see one year later you can connect 5 mins with that amount?  So price has to be flat, no?  Non-crypto people don't want to buy some coin at some exchange which fluctuates.  They want to buy minutes of online wifi time with their paypal (or MAYBE in some future with some major non-fluctuating cryptocurrency like bitcoin).  Just a coin for one purpose?  So how much I do like the idea, I don't see the coin itself getting much higher price gains (in the end because good ideas & good ico's ALWAYS get you profit in the beginning  ) since it would harm the system/hold back its useability when a non-major currency is used.  Your thoughts?

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, thanks for your questions.  So first of all if the non-crypto people want to buy WiC to use it, they won't hold it for a year. If they do they are not really buying for using it but to speculate. Also, the $value that they spend will remain the same. In your example, if someone buys 100 WiC for $100 and pays $5 for a WiFi network and suppose the price/WiC decreases after a year to 100 WiC = $50. Now he will still pay $5 for that network but with 10 WiC instead of 5 WiC he used a year earlier. So the payment is $ value will always remain the same.  We have future updates planned that will allow users to buy WiC with credit/debit cards. Another thing we plan to introduce is have WiC reloadable cards (something like gift cards) that will be available at local stores so that the non-crypto people can buy WiC with local currencies and use them in the app without knowing anything about crypto.  Also, I wouldn't call Bitcoin a non-fluctuating currency. Crypto is new and volatility is part of it and unfortunately no coin today is immune to it. Hopefully in the future when the market matures, we will have less volatility.  Thanks!

Author: niceli
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: I've asked myself the same question. But I have this question in general for a lot of projects: How are you able to distribute / generate new tokens within the app if (almost) all tokens have been distributed long before the application launch?  Also, how could you offer a stable fiat/token conversion on the app if the token price is varying a lot on the exchanges? And how would you tackle the issue with selling token within the app when 1$ might not be much for someone in the US or Europe but a lot for somebody in China?

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: We will not be selling tokens in the app ourselves. Meaning we will not be the ones that users pay. It will be other users that want to sell their tokens. We will just be the ones providing the service that will accept credit/debit cards. So for example if you want to buy 5$ worth WiC with your debit card, we will accept that payment, buy BTC with it, convert it to WiC on exchanges and forward that WiC to the buyer. So in effect, the buyer has paid with his debit card and received WiC. This is just an overview of the service and might change when development is closer.  Also, the price of the token with be volatile but since it is divisible the $ value can be maintained. Meaning if you want to buy 1$ worth WiC and WiC is worth $0.50, you will buy 2 WiC. If the price goes to $1/WiC you will still be buying $1 worth but get 1 WiC now.

Author: den_penta
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: For my first message in this forum some math:  I have 60MBs unlimited Internet connection at my home. Pay monthly about $6 (may vary because I pay bills in other currency).  So, in fact real people (me too) can use it from 8AM till 2AM 8^) It is about 18 hour per day. 540 hours per month.  If I will lease all this channel for people around self-cost should be: $6/540=$0,01(1)   or WiC 1,38 (if WiC price is $0,008) ~ WiC 0,46 (if WiC price is $0,024) per hour on full speed.  Just to put here some real digits...   BTW: big question is: 1. isolation of WiC traffic from WiFi-owner personal traffic and 2. possibility to share just part of the bandwidth.      for ex.: I can share 10~20 Mbs by any (low) price. But I'll think twice if it will be possible to share only all 60MBs

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Quote from: Blackcloud on August 18, 2017, 01:17:36 AM How do you deal with security problem? and same with previous post question, what if the owner shut it down after receiving the token?  Hey, so as of now how the app is developed, it will make the payment as soon as you  connect for the first time. So if the WiFi owner changes the password while you are connected you will lose the connection and would have already paid. Although this will be a very rare scenario since the  uploader will need to continuously monitor if someone connected and then change the password when they do. Also, since it will be only a few dollars worth, there is no real incentive to do this. Also, the planned feature update of having the uploader specify a minimum and maximum time and data limit for the connection will solve this issue for good. As for the security part, we gave special attention to it while developing the app. If you see the demo video on our site, you will realize that the end user is not even shown the password of the WiFi and the app handles the connection directly. Also, this is all done in an encrypted an safe manner.  Thanks!

Author: Elkmar
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Ok, and a system like, you are in an airport waiting for your plane, the airport wifi is fucked up (happens everytime). You share your 3g/4g via WiC. Your position is given via the map, you can't move while sharing, and it is precised it's a 3g/4g connection that is shared.  Maybe the system could work differently for this type of connexions, like the owner of the connection receive a notification like : Person A wants to use your connection for 10minutes, do you accept the transaction ? 50% Given at the beginning of the contract, 50% given at the end. Like this if the owner moves before the 10 minutes, Person A just paid 50% and can leave a bad rating, and if person A moves before the 10 minutes, the owner can leave a bad rating for the user, saying he moved before the end.  Well, that's just an idea, maybe it is really hard to create. But sometimes you just want internet to fast check messenger and mails for 5 minute.

Body: This is actually a very cool project. I especially like the low price  There is something I'm wondering about. With a limited number of coins/tokens what happens when people run out? Because at one point in the future, the cost of the coins might be larger then the cost of alternative wi-fi systems.

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, thanks!  When people run out of tokens, supply and demand takes over and they have to purchase WiC for use in our app. This will constantly raise the value of WiC as our app grows in popularity.  Also, ONLY WiC will be accepted as payment in the app since that is what gives it real inherent value.  As for the price, the user uploading the network can change it anytime he wishes so that it always remains the same in USD value. For example, if 1 WiC= $1 and you set the price at 1 WiC. After a while if the price rises to 1 WiC = $2, the you would just need to adjust the WiFi price to 0.5 WiC

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, as far as issues regarding illegal activity are concerned, there is no real incentive to use our app for illegal purposes since it would create unnecessary issues for that person. He could easily go to a Starbucks or McDonalds and use their WiFi; no reason to download this app, then buy WiC and then pay for it. Also, since our main aim is mass adoption, we have made it extremely easy and secure for the users. They don't need to worry about security concerns since if you have seen our app demo, you will realize that the end user does not have to do anything except click on a WiFi and buy it. Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey,  So how it works is you can rent out your WiFi network to anyone in need via our CryptoWi app. When you upload your WiFi network to the app, you get 100 WiC as a reward for that. You can also set a custom price in WiC for that network which you will earn if anyone else connects to it. So for example, if you set the price at 50 WiC, another user who wants to use your WiFi will have to pay you this amount first and then use the WiFi.  Let me know if you have further questions.  Also, check out our new explainer video:

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: That is true, the app connects without displaying the password to the end user as can also be seen in our demo video.  But I think he is asking what happens when someone other than the owner of the WiFi uploads the password. Maybe a friend or a relative who has the password. So the way the app is designed, anybody having the password of any network can upload it and earn WiC. But to be on the correct side, we will have a point in our app's terms and conditions that when you upload any password you confirm that you are the owner of that WiFi or have express permission from the owner to upload it. If that is not the case the user is in violation of the terms and solely responsible for the actions he undertakes.

Author: Muisde
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: I read the white paper and i think that WIC is a really interesting project, and your team look motivated ! I wish my neighbors will be a WIC user so i can try it.  I’ve got few questions : -   How could you know that passwords are correct ? You can’t go in any places to try each password. -   What happened if i change my password ? -   Is there a limit to the number of connected people a wifi can have ? -   Is there a limit to the data people can download ?  I wish you to success

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, thanks for your questions. Ok so if you have a look at our demo video posted, we actually try to put in a wrong password and show that the app gives an error and accepts only the correct password. If the password is changed later on, the buyer will not be able to connect and hence the uploader will not be paid. We don't limit the number of connections per WiFi but you could do it if you wish so. Also, there is no limit to the data that can be used.  Thanks!

Author: helloal
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: WiC looks like a one-of-a-kind project and seems promising. The novel idea of tapping into the modern person's need for readily accessible and available internet is a great idea, and probably will be very popular among tourists and office workers who want to work mobile.  In my eyes, this project would only be a 'good' project if the extent of it was just having people's personal wifi internet access, but what makes this project a great is that there is even more planned on the roadmap - namely having reloadable cards and partnering with travel agencies. The future roadmap looks realistic and not too overly ambitious for the project team size (but extra help will be needed especially when partnering with agencies all across the globe).  The ICO seems like a modest amount and not overly greedy.  Looking forward to using the app in the future

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, So our app is going to be launched worldwide and the primary target market is tourists and travelers. Yes 4G is getting popular but if you consider the entire world it is nowhere close to be the leading technology. 4G network is reliable only in a limited number of cities, and most either don't have any 4G or have patchy connectivity or are just too expensive. Also, when you are traveling that 4G won't work since you will be in roaming. Hence, our app will solve all these issues and provide users with reliable and affordable WiFi.

Author: Rimus
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: The project looks very interested but I have one question.     How do you plan to prevent abusing public Wi-Fi spots (coffee shop, restaurant, airports etc). There are a lot of spots operated by people not involved in WiC project and without any knowledge about cryptocurrency.  One smart guy could visit such spots, submit their passwords into WiC database and earn their money.  Is there any limits for number of passwords one person allowed to submit to WiC application?

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey,  Thanks for your question. So firstly, most of the cafes, restaurants etc. that have WiFI for their customers only keep the WiFi open and ask their customers to log in via a web portal and our app won't support this. But yes, the way the app is designed anybody having the password of any network can upload it and earn WiC. But to be on the correct side, we will have a point in our app's terms and conditions that when you upload any password you confirm that you are the owner of that WiFi or have express permission from the owner to upload it. Also, no there is no limit on the number of passwords a user can upload.

Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, I am curious about your project. I also asked in the German Topic, but I just want to ask here again some questions.  First of all, how do you want to handel Wifi abuse like for example if someone is hand in someone others wifi data and try to get paid for this? Someone other than the owener can fill in these informations and get paid for it.  Second how do you want to handel problems with abuse of wifi like someone is using internet through your service and downloads some illegal stuff, the owner get problems for this but hasn't done anything.  Greetings!

Author: CoinCollector006
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hello, I don't normally invest in ICOs, but this looks unique and much higher quality than many of the Ethereum ICOs I have observed (Useless Ether Token, Ferrari coin e.g. fund the purchase of the dev's ferrari ICO, etc)  https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2023069.0  1. Could one of the developers list out some of the security precautions that are being implemented as part of this platform>? The passwords are described as encryteed. Are there any other safeguards to allay concerns about security?  2. Is there a Wi Coin website and white paper? If so where can they be found?  3. What happens if a user attempts to monetize a Wifi network that they don't own, e.g. a restaurant they visited ? Is there a mechanism to prevent abuses?

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey,  Thanks for your questions. So firstly, most of the cafes, restaurants etc. that have WiFI for their customers only keep the WiFi open and ask their customers to log in via a web portal and our app won't support this. But yes there will always be a few places which keep the same password over time and intend to make it available only to customers. For a second just forget about the app and think about it. Will you be able to take the password once and share it with all your friends and you all could use that WiFi forever (since the password is not being changed) even when you are no longer customers? So you see that can happen even without the app. But to be on the correct side, we will have a point in our app's terms and conditions that when you upload any password you confirm that you are the owner of that WiFi or have express permission from the owner to upload it.  As for the second question, the first thing to understand is that there is zero incentive for anyone to use our app for illegal stuff since it would create unnecessary issues for him. He will first have to download the app, buy WiC, navigate to the WiFi and then pay for it and do the illegal stuff. it would make much more sense for him to go to a Starbucks and use their WiFi. It is the same logic that prevents 51% attacks on the Bitcoin network, a person with enough resources could do it but it wouldn't be beneficial to him to do so. Anyways, assuming that someone still goes ahead and does it, it will be the same like that person going to starbucks and doing it. The way the owner of the WiFi (Starbucks) is not at fault, the same way the WiFi owner will not be at fault.  Hope that clarifies it. Thanks!

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Haha didn't know about the ferrari coin  And thanks for appreciating our project!  1) I am more of a PR guy but from what I remember, everything happening on the app is all encrypted. Secondly, the password is not revealed to the end user and the app handles the connection. Thirdly, we have an anti-bot mechanism which will detect and ban users trying to use bots to upload passwords. Next, we have also made it so mobile hotspots cannot be uploaded and only WiFi connections are accepted. We have also made the app in such a way that only correct and working WiFi networks get paid and can be connected to.  2) The website is listed in the OP - www.cryptowi.com and the whitepaper will be released along with the Token Sale details in a few days - https://www.cryptowi.com/whitepaper  3) The way the app is built, anybody who knows the password of a WiFi can upload it and earn WiC. Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: FAQ posted in the OP - https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2043933.msg20353036#msg20353036   1) What stage is the development at? We decided it would be best if we have something real when we announce this project and not just an idea on a paper. Hence, you will be happy to know that we have a fully developed and working app ready to be launched. You can view the app demo on our website: https://www.cryptowi.com  2) Where will the CryptoWi app be available and when can I download it? We will be launching the app worldwide shortly after the Token Sale is over.  3) Is the app secure enough? I am worried about my privacy! We developed the app giving special attention to the safety and privacy of users. Everything is encrypted and the end user is not even shown the password for the WiFi network he/she is connecting to. The app handles everything securely.  4) What will happen when someone buys a network which doesn't work? As seen in our demo video, when you try to enter a wrong password the app doesn't allow it. Only correct and working networks can be bought or sold! You can be sure that you will pay ONLY IF THE NETWORK WORKS!  5) What if someone uploads an open and already free WiFi network? This is not possible with our app since only networks with passwords can be uploaded. The app won't accept open networks.  6) Sounds like a good project with high potential, how can I invest? The Token Sale details have not been announced yet. Please subscribe to be the first to know when exact details are announced: https://www.cryptowi.com/token-sale  7) Will the Token Sale be escrowed? Yes, both the Presale and Token Sale will be fully escrowed by extremely reputed members of the community. Wait for further announcements.

As for your question, the team is actually bigger than what is posted and only the lead from each department is posted. We are getting legal advise and also hiring some legal experts because of the complex environment regarding Token Sales and will publish details once we get the go ahead from legal. You might know that making an app (that too this complex) is not a one man job and Deepak is just the development team lead. There are around a total of 12-15 members in the team including full time employees, independent contractors and interns. Also, since we have actually gone ahead, spent money and time and developed a real product rather than just showing you a 100 page document with complex terms, I would say it is not all that suspicious. Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey,  Since our main aim is mass adoption, we have made it extremely easy and secure for the users. We have tough security measures in place and are pretty sure they will not be breakable but like anything in the world there is always a little chance that it can be hacked. Even government agencies, elections, government websites and everything else has been hacked at one point in history so we cannot say it is impossible but it is highly unlikely and unrewarding for anyone to waste resources to break into our app security and do something that he could have done by going to a Starbucks!  Also users don't need to worry about security concerns since if you have seen our app demo, you will realize that the end user does not have to do anything except click on a WiFi and buy it. The app does the rest and connects directly without exposing any details (including the password) to the end user. Also this is all encrypted and transmitted in a safe manner.  Users will be able to register via Facebook, Gmail or traditional email ids.  We have our Token Sale coming up soon, subscribe to stay updated: https://www.cryptowi.com/token-sale Thanks!

Author: rsa
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: WiC is a daring concept.  People are not worried about just "sharing wifi/email/corporate password" but the real concern is implications that can arise due to the misuse of resources.  Sharing your WiFi is risk because you are sharing your router to an unknown person who may have all sort of intentions; from general browsing to news channels to monitoring your wifi camera and intruding Government systems.  If WiC's app can be a guardian against all these, this would become a great project.

Author: Korsakopf
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Good point, there should be some security in place so that the person you are sharing your wifi with wont be able to access devices on your home network.

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey,  Since our main aim is mass adoption, we have made it extremely easy and secure for the users. They don't need to worry about security concerns since if you have seen our app demo, you will realize that the end user does not have to do anything except click on a WiFi and buy it. The app does the rest and connects directly without exposing any details (including the password) to the end user. Also this is all encrypted and transmitted in a safe manner. Hence, users don't need to worry about anyone accessing their devices from the shared WiFi.  Also, there is no real incentive for anybody to use our app for wrong purposes as it would be better and easier for him to just use a free public WiFi rather than download our app, buy WiC, then find an available network, then hack our security and do something wrong. Author: heyjoe
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Read through quite a bit of the thread - looks like you are well-organized and prepared.  The demo is a major selling point here.  Having a working product, especially in our current environment, shows you have put in an investment up front and explains clearly the goal of the project.  A couple questions/concerns for you - forgive me if I missed the answers:  1. Do you have LinkedIn profiles for your founders? Particularly interested in your marketing and sales team since coordination of agreements with gas stations, travel agencies, etc. is a large scale sales project.  2. I have seen you mentioned WiFi sharing as a large industry already, but this is an area that many users will be nervous about.  Connecting to unknown networks or offering up your own network without having an understanding of how to properly set up security is putting not only the computers on the network at risk but also opening up your connection to potentially illegal activity.  Why would a 'regular user' want to take that risk?  When a regular person connects to public WiFi at a Starbucks (for example) they have a feeling of security due to the way those networks are configured.   Overall, the concept is nice and you have a demo which is a huge plus, but looking to understand how you are going to overcome security concerns to gain traction with a less technical userbase.

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, thanks for taking the time to go through our project. Yes, we decided to get a demo ready so that people know what they are investing in and what they can expect. We realized it is not correct and ethical to have a fancy roadmap stretching years and nothing concrete to base it on.  As for your questions, the team is actually bigger than what is posted and only the lead from each department is posted. We are getting legal advise and also hiring some legal experts because of the complex environment regarding Token Sales and will publish details once we get the go ahead from legal. You might know that making an app (that too this complex) is not a one man job and Deepak is just the development team lead. There are around a total of 12-15 members in the team including full time employees, independent contractors and interns. Also, you are right that partnering with gas stations and retail outlets will be a challenge and that is one of the reasons we are looking to raise money in the upcoming Token Sale.  WiFi sharing is in fact a huge industry with a user base of more than 50 million already. As far as issues regarding illegal activity are concerned, there is no real incentive to use our app for illegal purposes since it would create unnecessary issues for that person. He could easily go to a Starbucks or McDonalds and use their WiFi; no reason to download this app, then buy WiC and then pay for it. Also, since our main aim is mass adoption, we have made it extremely easy and secure for the users. They don't need to worry about security concerns since if you have see our app demo, you will realize that the end user does not have to do anything except click on a WiFi and buy it. The app does the rest and connects directly without exposing any details to the end user. Also this is all encrypted.  If you have any further questions, don't hesitate to post here or PM me. To stay updated please subscribe: https://www.cryptowi.com/token-sale  Thanks!

Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, that is a good question. And you are correct when you think that the reason for this Token Sale is to get capital to fund this project. The reason why there is no minimum requirement is:  1) We have already invested our own money and developed a working product that is ready for launch. 2) The app itself can be monetized and can provide a regular source of income. 3) Why, the Token Sale then? Because we need the capital to expedite marketing and further development of the project. If less amount is raised the project will be less marketed and slow to say. If we sell out on the other hand, we will speed up everything and will not need to wait for the app to generate revenue required in order for us to grow. 4) Also, the max cap will be well under 5 million dollars because we do not need it for R&D related costs but for improving a developed product and marketing it on a global scale. The Token Sale amount will also be used to secure strategic partnerships with travel agencies and convenience store and gas station chains in order to promote CryptoWi.  If you have any further questions, feel free to ask them. Also, to stay up to date with all our announcements, please subscribe: https://www.cryptowi.com/token-sale  Thanks!

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey, you understood it right, with WiC everyone will be able to rent their WiFi networks.  As far as free networks all over the world are concerned, that is still years away and not at all guaranteed. It will require approval of the world's governments and huge investments which makes it uncertain to say the least. And even then, people will still use WiFi networks, all the service provider companies won't go bankrupt overnight   Also, even if there is no free internet worldwide, you might think what about the developed countries where cafes, etc. have free WiFi. Now since our app aims to monetize WiFi sharing, the main aim is to market it aggressively to tourists and travelers. Tourists will not know where free WiFi is in the city they are visiting and hence the CryptoWi app will come in handy. Also, there are still a huge number of cities worldwide including in developed countries where free WiFi is not very easily available. Only selected big cities really have enough free WiFi networks.  Also, most of these cafes, hotels and cinemas have free WiFi "ONLY FOR CUSTOMERS" which really does not mean free.  Hope I answered your question, please feel free to ask me any more question.  Also, subscribe to stay updated: https://www.cryptowi.com/token-sale  Thanks!

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Ok let me source this from the website's section titled "Why invest in WiC?"  1) When you invest in WiC, you are investing in something that is real and already developed, not a pipe-dream. We have worked very hard to get you something complete and real and hence the chances of success increase manifold.  2) We are not asking for thousands of BTCs for our project and that reduces the total initial market cap of the coin. At the ICO price, the market cap of WiC will be well under 5 million dollars (exact price will be out soon) which is around the 200+ mark on coinmarketcap.com. Evidently, our project is better and worth more than most of the coins with a higher market cap than that and hence there is a very good chance that your investment will give you a huge ROI on launch.  3) There is no crypto currency today that has anything even similar to what we are offering with WiC and CryptoWi and hence WiC will be the first and only player in this untapped market. As a result, the potential and room for growth is tremendous.  4) With a potential ready user base of more than 50 million, WiC is very likely to succeed and revolutionize the WiFi sharing industry. As more people start to buy WiC to use it in the CryptoWi app, the early investors are expected to receive the best returns.  5) Since Wi Coins (WiC) is the ONLY accepted method of payment in the app, anybody wanting to use it will have to buy WiC first, naturally increasing its value.  6) WiC is one of the very few crypto currencies today with a real world use case which gives it real value. In the long run, only such currencies are likely to succeed.  Hope that gives you confidence that Token Sale investors have a very very good chance of getting huge ROI with WiC.

Yes that should be available.  - How will you facilitate adoption on the buy side ? In my view, the app should allow the user to buy Wic against USD. To facilitate adoption we have the 100 WiC per correct password initiative for the first 50,000 passwords. We plan to have WiC reloadable cards available for purchase at convenience stores and gas stations later. We also intend to partner with travel agencies around the world who would promote our project to their clients increasing its value. Also, WiC is the only accepted currency in our app and hence anyone wanting to use it will have to buy WiC first, naturally increasing its value. As for trading against USD, that will be possible on launch with one of our partner's services at CryptoDao.  - can't you release the App on the appstore prior to the ICO so that users can test it ? Sorry, but the app will be released after the Token Sale. We have the demo available which is much more than most of the other projects who just have a fancy Whitepaper and nothing real.

Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Important Links  App Download: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.cryptowi.cryptowi  Exchanges:  Livecoin.net: BTC: https://www.livecoin.net/en/trade/index?currencyPair=WIC%2FBTC ETH: https://www.livecoin.net/en/trade/index?currencyPair=WIC%2FETH  EtherDelta ETH: https://etherdelta.com/#WIC-ETH  Token Store ETH: https://token.store/WIC  Coinmarketcap: https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/wi-coin/#markets   Website          Facebook          Twitter          Telegram          Whitepaper   Wi Coin (WiC) is a coin that will bring crypto to the masses. Today, 99% of the people involved in crypto currencies use it either as a speculative asset or hoard it with a dream of becoming a millionaire overnight. This is the primary reason for the lack of adoption and WiC is a coin that will solve this issue. WiC will give the average person a reason to buy and use crypto in his everyday life. Introducing the killer app of the crypto world, “CryptoWi”, an app which rewards its users in Wi Coins (WiC) for doing what they do every day, use their Wi-Fi! This is how it works:   First, you will need to create an account to use the app and earn and store your WiCs.   Second, the user can upload passwords of the Wi-Fi connections from the "WiFi" tab as shown above. The user is awarded 100 WiC per correct password uploaded in order to grow the network initially. The user will also be able to set a custom price in WiC for each of these networks. Anybody who wants to connect to these networks will have to pay this amount and it will be credited to the original password uploader. This gives an added incentive to people for not changing the password and helps the community grow larger. 5,000,000 WiC have been reserved for distribution to the users in the early stages of the app to grow the user base. At 100 coins per password, this will be 50,000 passwords.   The “Map” tab shows the number of available WiFi passwords at any location in the world and can be searched for by the user. The user will also be able to navigate to these wifi spots in offline mode in the future.      We are launching WiC as an Ethereum ERC20 token. Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: 1) What stage is the development at? We decided it would be best if we have something real when we announce this project and not just an idea on a paper. Hence, you will be happy to know that we have a fully developed and working app ready to be launched. You can view the app demo on our website: https://www.cryptowi.com  2) Where will the CryptoWi app be available and when can I download it? We will be launching the app worldwide shortly after the Token Sale is over.  3) Is the app secure enough? I am worried about my privacy! We developed the app giving special attention to the safety and privacy of users. Everything is encrypted and the end user is not even shown the password for the WiFi network he/she is connecting to. The app handles everything securely.  4) What will happen when someone buys a network which doesn't work? As seen in our demo video, when you try to enter a wrong password the app doesn't allow it. Only correct and working networks can be bought or sold! You can be sure that you will pay ONLY IF THE NETWORK WORKS!  5) What if someone uploads an open and already free WiFi network? This is not possible with our app since only networks with passwords can be uploaded. The app won't accept open networks.  6) Sounds like a good project with high potential, how can I invest? The Presale begins on August 15 at 4PM EST. Details are available at: https://www.cryptowi.com/token-sale  7) Will the Token Sale be escrowed? Yes, both the Presale and Token Sale will be fully escrowed by extremely reputed members of the community, minerjones, Blazed and the cryptocurrency exchange Livecoin.net. Details are available at: https://www.cryptowi.com/token-sale

Author: Lambo06
Title: 🔥⭐[ANN] WiC|Monetizing WiFi Sharing| ⭐🔥 App Launched! 🔥⭐
Body: Hey,  Ok so first of all there is no real incentive to use our app for illegal purposes since it would create unnecessary issues for that person. He could easily go to a Starbucks or McDonalds and use their WiFi; no reason to download this app, then buy WiC and then pay for it. Also, WiFi sharing is already a HUGE industry with millions of users worldwide, we are monetizing it and tapping this huge market.  As far as identifying targets, it is not necessary at all that the app user has loads of crypto with him/her. This app could be the only crypto related thing in his world. Also, its no different than having cash in your pocket. If someone is going to mug you, it is more probable that your phone and cash are more valuable than the WiC inside the app.
